# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PyAudio Installation (for Voice Input)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# âš ï¸ PyAudio is OPTIONAL but needed for voice features
#
# WINDOWS:
#   Method 1 - Using pipwin (Recommended):
#     pip install pipwin
#     pipwin install pyaudio
#
#   Method 2 - Download pre-built wheel:
#     Visit: https://www.lfd.uci.edu/~gohlke/pythonlibs/#pyaudio
#     Download appropriate .whl file for your Python version
#     pip install pyaudioâ€‘0.2.13â€‘cp311â€‘cp311â€‘win_amd64.whl
#
# MACOS:
#   Install portaudio first:
#     brew install portaudio
#   Then install PyAudio:
#     pip install pyaudio
#
# LINUX (Ubuntu/Debian):
#   Install system dependencies:
#     sudo apt-get update
#     sudo apt-get install python3-pyaudio
#   OR build from source:
#     sudo apt-get install portaudio19-dev
#     pip install pyaudio
#
# LINUX (Fedora/RedHat):
#   sudo dnf install portaudio-devel
#   pip install pyaudio
#
# If PyAudio fails, the app will still work WITHOUT voice features.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Groq API Client (Optional - for Groq Llama model)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# If you want to use Groq's API client library instead of requests:
#   pip install groq>=0.5.0
#
# Otherwise, the app uses requests library which is already included.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Testing Installation
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# After installing, test with:
#   python -c "import google.genai; print('âœ“ Gemini OK')"
#   python -c "import requests; print('âœ“ Requests OK')"
#   python -c "import speech_recognition; print('âœ“ Speech Recognition OK')"
#   python -c "import pyttsx3; print('âœ“ TTS OK')"
#   python -c "import PyPDF2; print('âœ“ PDF OK')"
#   python -c "import PIL; print('âœ“ Pillow OK')"
#
# =============================================================================
# ðŸ”§ TROUBLESHOOTING
# =============================================================================
#
# Issue: "No module named 'tkinter'"
# Solution: Tkinter is part of Python standard library
#   Windows: Reinstall Python with "tcl/tk and IDLE" option checked
#   Linux: sudo apt-get install python3-tk
#   macOS: Should be included by default
#
# Issue: "SSL Certificate Error" with requests
# Solution: pip install --upgrade certifi
#
# Issue: "Import Error" for google.genai
# Solution: pip install --upgrade google-genai
#
# Issue: Voice features not working
# Solution: Check microphone permissions in system settings
#
# =============================================================================
